manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Sennheiser ACCENTUM Wireless Play by your own rules. No matter where life takes you, ACCENTUM ensures superior sound on-the-go with hybrid ANC and up to 50 hours of playtime for every audio journey.

Unrivaled 50-hour battery playtime. Keep the music flowing for days on a single charge No matter where life takes you, ACCENTUM ensures that your soundtrack never fades away. From dawn till dusk, enjoy up to 50hrs of captivating sounds with full ANC on. When is finally time to charge, our fast-charge feature gives you 5hrs playtime in 10 minutes so you can power up on the go.

Sennheiser sound – your audio journey. Indulge in captivating sound, thanks to the 37mm driver Engineered in Germany, Sennheiser’s unique acoustic design delivers a superior audio experience. Enjoy crisp, deep bass and brilliant highs. Feel every note, every beat, and every emotion as if you’re centerstage.

Tune in to your tunes, not the noise! Get lost in music with our Hybrid Active Noise Cancellation Whether hustling through a busy street or seeking alone time in a crowded place, our ANC technology ensures your audio journey remains uninterrupted. When you need to stay in touch with reality without disconnecting from your music, Transparency Mode lets you do just that.

All-day comfort, every day. Designed for marathon-long listening sessions Cushioned earcups hug your ears, while the soft-touch silicon-lined headband ensures a secure fit without compromising on comfort. Whether it's throughout your daily commute or a late-night groove, ACCENTUM stays in place softly on your ears, accompanying your audio journey.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Nice sound, decent batter life, not very heavy, and very comfortable to wear. All for a rather decent price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars GREAT sound and quality for price
reviews.reviewText: Compared to higher-end alternatives (AirPod MAX or other Sennheiser models) there are noticeable differences in the construction of these (most components are plastic) but don’t let that sway you. The sound is amazing, they are super comfortable to wear, and the microphone is clear if you are using for work or regular use headphones for both music and calls. Highly recommend. Best headphones you can buy for <$200.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Best budget headphones with one major defect!
reviews.reviewText: These are the best budget headphones, very light weight, super comfortable even when used for long time, feels high quality. The only major defect I see in these headphones are the volume levels…I see the same issue in momentum 4’s as well that is reason I have returned those…same issue with accentums as well…not sure why sennheiser do not consider this defect to fix or may be that’s how it’s designed…we only feel fuller sound when the volume is 100 percent…if the volume is below 80 you feel nothing…the volume we get for 100 usually need to be at 75-80 level…if this is fixed no other headphones even very expensive which are out in current market can beat these headphones. I may return because of the unsatisfied volume levels.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very good sounding but it’s a bit quiet
reviews.reviewText: I first got these headphones for outside use because I never tried anc headphones before. I got some wireless ones so a cable doesn’t have to tangle around. When I got them it was very nice but I played some music and it was super quiet when you use it on a phone. When I connect it to my computer, everything was fine and I can make it way louder.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great sound and comfort!
reviews.reviewText: I got these since I like to listen to music in public areas but unable to have anything inside my ears so no earbuds. The inner ear area is large enough at 65mm tall and the padding is super soft and doesn't bother me while wearing glasses. They can get warm but the cushion is easily wiped down from any sweat if you're in a hot environment. Best thing I've gotten myself all year!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 12, 2023
reviews.reviewText: not very loud, noise cancelation isnt powerful, but SQ is good, they are comfy and light, i would recommend

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Great sound, comfort, & noise cancelling. Highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Stopped holding charge
reviews.reviewText: These headphones seemed to be high quality when they first arrived. I needed them for air travel and occasional use. They were too tight for long term comfort, and only were used 1-2 times per week.I read reviews that they would be comfortable for a larger head, but I could never wear them for long. Just after 30 day return window, they started making crackling/or skipping sounds while listening and have stopped holding charge. I'm not sure if I just received a faulty device, but for the price, it's beyond annoying, and I'm not even sure I will get product support.

I started a return because it came with a buzzing noise when turned on. This buzzing was an issue I had with low quality headphones I tried before but I never though sennheiser would not have this since I really like their earbuds (true wireless1). Idk why it has that noise if its the active noise cancelling which cannot be turned off only switched to transparency mode which is really annoying. The headphones were packed very poorly so they could have been knocked around during shipping but it could have just been bad wiring that is making the buzzing noise.
Very comfortable to wear, and the sound quality is great. I can't give it full marks on the active noise-cancelling; it is good but not perfect.

Light weight on my head, sound is very good, as always with Sennheiser. App is good as well, it's just that the ANC on & off from the headphone button is not available on this model. Aside from that, all is good on Accentum!

reviews.reviewTitle: Excelente sonido pero me duraron poco.
reviews.reviewText: Sonido increible,claro,preciso y bajos resonantes que no afectan a la experiencia general,pero ya es la 3ra vez que un producto sennheiser que me falla en mi experiencia,si buscas calidad de sonido y bajos estos pueden ser los tuyos.
